width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/upokiloki.showPublicProfile?language=EN>poki loki</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/22/02 3:05:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=803.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> sorry to say</span><hr size=1> yea ummm there are ppl like me that well suck at grammer and i dont no all the rules and crap and well i like to make stories and for a fact my story i said i plan to make into a manga so it is basicly a outline so i can make my manga when i ready and this is so that i dont forget it i dont care if no one wants to read it right now if they hate that i cant do grammer and other things then dont read it they arent really making much of an effort to read my story because it is sorta more straight forward on what is really goin on and i try my best i put a effort because if you read my preface it has like no punctuation and stuff so i tried and your saying put an effort i did sorry to say but i hate all that crap and i have never been able to do it good but i have always be complimented on my stories if you dont wanna read it i aint lossing anything and what not your just not reading a story so once again I DONT CARE!!! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/upokiloki.showPublicProfile?language=EN>poki loki</A> at: 9/22/02 3:10:22 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/upopularmisconception.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Popular Misconception</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/22/02 4:31:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=803.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sorry to say</span><hr size=1> Grammar isn't hard to use.  Get a book if you don't know or get help from someone who does know. There's some links in the sticky thread at the top. <br><br>If it's an outline there are better ways to do it, clear and conscise notes on index cards are better. If you've ever scribbled something down and not been able to read it back later, this is the story equivalent. <br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> if you dont wanna read it i aint lossing anything<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br><br>I'm the only one to respond to this thread.  You've possibly lost your only crit on this website. <br><br>Look, I may sound like an arse, but I take language seriously and I'm trying to save you from some trouble, possibly embarrassment, later on.   <br><br> <p><img src=http://www.kgmander.50megs.com/images/sig.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/upokiloki.showPublicProfile?language=EN>poki loki</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/22/02 5:09:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=803.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sorry to say</span><hr size=1> acctually i have 2 editors ( friends of mine ) that said they would help me out and fix it up so :P on u ^^ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/urichied.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RichieD</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/23/02 4:23:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=803.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> He's right you know.</span><hr size=1> If you call yourself a writer, then what you are saying is that you can use words to paint pictures, to create emotions. If you can't use words to make proper sentences, then you've already lost half the battle.<br><br>The thing that makes it worse is that every computer with a word processor probably has a spell-checker. If you are writing a story or a script then it's not that hard to do the basic checks. When I see a writer that hasn't done that, especially on the internet, I automatically begin to assume that this writer is some kid for whom writing is just a month-long phase and who doesn't care enough about the craft to make sure it's done properly. Most of the times I skip those stories, because if he doesn't care enough, why should I?<br><br>Compare it to the art section on any messageboard. The people who you can tell are serious are the ones who make sure the lines are straight, that they didn't use lined paper, who planned their drawings before they drew. If that person does not draw perfect anatomy, I can tell he is willing to put in the time it takes to learn. <br><br>If a writer does not take the time to work on his grammar, what reason do I have for thinking that he/she would take the time to work out any issues with plotting that he/she might have. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/utarotgirl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TarotGirl</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fresh Meat</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/25/02 9:47:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=803.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> My two cents</span><hr size=1> Anything with poor grammer becomes a chore to read. If you think your stuff is so good that you don't need to fix it or that if people don't want to wade through your grammer mistakes then you yourself aren't taking the work seriously and that's doing a great injustice to writing. If you are going to break a rule (mine is comma splicing because it's the style I use.. think poetry..) then you had better have a reason for it.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showNextMessage?topicID=803.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=803.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.emailToFriend?topicID=803.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.threadControl?topicID=803.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=803.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=803.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub25.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><s